She retreats into a place that is free from all other inputs so she can attune her ear to God.

26:20.032 --> 26:28.562
She can hear the God who's constantly speaking to her, but harder to hear in this busyness and noise of her ordinary life.

26:29.186 --> 26:36.193
Eastern Orthodox Bishop Koolistos Ware says, solitude is a state of inner tranquility or mental quietude and concentration.

26:36.233 --> 26:42.839
Not simply silence, but an attitude of listening to God and of openness to God.

26:43.499 --> 26:49.805
Is he ultimately, solitude is not so much about getting away from external conditions like noise and busyness.

26:50.146 --> 26:55.591
It's about the internal condition of yielding myself to God's voice.

26:56.091 --> 26:58.994
It's about yielded contentment

26:59.106 --> 27:01.410
to wherever God might lead me.

27:01.931 --> 27:18.317
It's about freedom from all of our attachments and compulsions, all of that dysregulated clinging that you and I do to convince ourselves that we need this and that in order to be okay when in reality those compulsions are the very things that are imprisoning us.

27:19.619 --> 27:24.787
Quiet solitude opens my ears to hear the whispers of God that I can't hear in noise and busyness.

27:25.148 --> 27:26.450
That's attentiveness.

