31:32.546 --> 31:40.379
John is the living fulfillment of an even more ancient prophetic promise from Isaiah, a voice of one calling out in the wilderness.

31:40.980 --> 31:43.524
Prepare the way for the Lord, make straight paths for him.

31:44.045 --> 31:58.770
Now this English word, wilderness, it's the Greek term, eremos, which can be translated as wilderness, solitary place, or secluded place.

31:58.914 --> 32:10.205
The son of a father who was driven into seclusion by divine force, and a mother who chose seclusion by divine consent, lives his entire life in seclusion, in solitude.

32:11.846 --> 32:13.728
And the Lord he's preparing the way for?

32:13.788 --> 32:22.256
The one he's making straight paths for his arrival were introduced to Jesus in his adulthood in the following chapter by Luke this way.

32:22.757 --> 32:28.082
Jesus, full of the Holy Spirit, left the Jordan, was led by the Spirit into the, what, friends?

32:29.154 --> 32:29.895
the wilderness.

32:31.497 --> 32:39.065
Jesus, full of the Holy Spirit, was driven into solitude, just like Zechariah and Elizabeth and John before him.

32:39.386 --> 32:46.154
You're beginning to see a pattern here about where God can be found, about where we are formed.

32:48.316 --> 32:51.600
Jesus' ministry was born from solitude.

32:52.861 --> 32:56.786
